I never thought of myself as a vintage girlie but as I’m sitting in my over 100 year old home and look around 80% of my jewlery, clothing and goods are vintage. Randomly stumbling into shops and asking locals where to go. Collecting what’s meant to be mine, not searching. Being around all of my treasures and wearing them brings a delightful tingle to my soul ✨

My most recent treasure is this basketball jersey from the early 60’s I found at @concrete_matter in Amsterdam. The earrings number 8 turquoise earrings from a reservation in Colorado. I wonder who wore them before me? Are we kindred souls, would be friends today? I like to think so 🤍
